Label and selector
==================
Lables : 
=> Labels are key-value pairs which are attached to pods, replication controller and services. 
=> They are used as identifying attributes for objects such as pods and replication controller. 
=> They can be added to an object at creation time and can be added or modified at the run time.

Selectors:
=> Labels do not provide uniqueness. In general, we can say many objects can carry the same labels.
=> Selectors are used by the users to select a set of objects. The label selector is the core grouping primitive in Kubernetes. 
=> Kubernetes API supports two types of selectors.
  a) Equality-based selectors : This allows filtering by key and value, where matching objects should satisfy all the specified labels.
  b) Set-based selectors : This allows filtering keys according to a set of values.


 







